WEBVTT

00:00.354 --> 00:00.955
All right.

00:00.995 --> 00:08.326
Well, because we jumped into the next series, we don't have a bumper video tonight.

00:08.366 --> 00:09.408
We don't thank you so much.

00:09.748 --> 00:11.731
We don't have any of that exciting stuff.

00:11.751 --> 00:15.337
So we're going to just jump right in to the Word of God.

00:15.377 --> 00:15.958
Is that all right?

00:17.139 --> 00:17.921
Let me try that again.

00:17.961 --> 00:20.845
We're just going to jump right in to the Word of God tonight.

00:20.885 --> 00:21.586
Is that all right?

00:22.082 --> 00:23.305
Hey, there you go.

00:23.626 --> 00:25.029
Hey, we're in a series.

00:25.049 --> 00:28.437
We just wrapped up a series that we've called built to last.

00:28.457 --> 00:34.130
We've taken the time over the last several weeks to discover what it means to truly

00:34.242 --> 00:38.927
dig in to the Word of God to build on a solid foundation.

00:39.067 --> 00:45.934
If you're like me, you've been a part of things and been places where they didn't really build something to last.

00:45.954 --> 00:50.780
It was kind of a wiggle wobble type of fixture that barely stood on its own.

00:50.840 --> 01:00.530
I remember one time I was at staff at another church and one of the workers in the church had her husband come in and he put together a little coffee stand

01:00.610 --> 01:18.251
and after he got done and left, we started looking at that and realized that he put the back of the fixture on backwards or upside down, and rather than taking the screws out and fixing it, he just broke the wood in the bottom because he figured that would work.

01:18.271 --> 01:21.675
And I think sometimes that's what we do as believers.

01:23.377 --> 01:27.922
Rather than saying, Lord, I want the best that you have

01:28.898 --> 01:31.221
Lord, I give you all that I am.

01:31.261 --> 01:37.269
We settle for things that have been put in upside down or even broken on the edge.

01:37.930 --> 01:42.175
And God says, I have something greater for you.

01:43.377 --> 01:56.914
See, this year we're talking about this idea of building his church, not so we can have a name for ourselves, not to promote anybody in this building, or even the church as a whole, but to build his church,

01:57.154 --> 02:01.939
where Jesus said the gates of hell will not even be able to shake it.

02:01.979 --> 02:04.462
It will not prevail against it.

02:05.423 --> 02:11.109
Now, one way that we can accomplish that task is by being a people of prayer.

02:11.389 --> 02:26.866
We were supposed to, as I stated a moment ago, begin this series the first Sunday of February, but as I began to process through this last night and even this morning, I realized how fitting it is that we're kicking off this series

02:26.946 --> 02:33.814
Now, because Sunday wraps up our 21 days of prayer and fasting.

02:35.276 --> 02:41.864
So tonight, we're going to kick off a series that we're simply calling a house of prayer.

02:41.964 --> 02:54.439
It flows directly out of our Build His Church theme for the year because if God is building His church, then prayer must be the foundation that we build upon.

02:56.542 --> 02:56.882
Right?

02:58.050 --> 03:00.473
You see, it's not enough for us to say, you know what?

03:00.674 --> 03:05.840
We're gonna build his church and we're gonna build it on an hour and 15 minutes a week.

03:08.224 --> 03:16.395
Or sometimes an hour and 15 minutes a month or every two weeks or periodically giving God time.

03:16.435 --> 03:22.162
But I believe that God has called us, you and me, and those are online and those in other locations.

03:22.202 --> 03:27.890
God's called every one of us to build his church, but to allow it to be built

03:28.194 --> 03:28.935
on prayer.

03:30.077 --> 03:55.154
I want to take some time to help us over the next several weeks to discover that prayer is not just for the select, well-educated, knowledgeable, not even just for a small group, but prayer is a key that has been given to all that have a desire, all that have a heart to draw closer and closer and closer to God.

03:56.354 --> 04:00.279
It would be easy right now in this room to say amen to that.

04:02.102 --> 04:02.603
Thank you.

04:04.125 --> 04:06.908
But truth be told, not always do we believe that.

04:09.031 --> 04:14.218
There are moments that we look at our lives and we begin to put doubts in our prayers.

04:14.239 --> 04:16.201
We begin to put doubt in ourselves.

04:16.241 --> 04:23.091
We look at our situations and we're not really sure that prayer applies to us.

04:23.431 --> 04:25.554
So we ask this very honest

04:25.826 --> 04:29.895
question, do I really have to pray?

04:31.840 --> 04:33.404
Have you ever asked yourself that question?

04:34.626 --> 04:36.872
Do I really have to pray?

04:36.912 --> 04:39.698
Yes, it's essential.

04:41.058 --> 04:45.185
It's not just optional, but it's a vital part of our walk with Christ.

04:45.205 --> 04:50.653
The truth be told, many of us don't really struggle with believing that prayer is effective.

04:51.074 --> 04:57.384
We struggle with believing that prayer actually matters or that it applies to us.

04:59.167 --> 05:06.418
We ask questions like this, if God already knows everything, then why do I need to pray?

05:08.098 --> 05:17.410
We may even ask this, if God is sovereign, if he is all known, if he holds everything together, why should I even try?

05:17.550 --> 05:20.494
I don't feel qualified, so what's the need?

05:20.594 --> 05:24.880
I don't feel spiritual, so why do I even give it an effort?

05:26.582 --> 05:28.585
I'm gonna be honest with you, these are fair questions.

05:30.648 --> 05:35.634
But I also believe that their distractions, that the enemy uses

05:35.714 --> 05:46.328
in his arsenal to derail us from utilizing the most powerful weapon, offensive and offensive weapon that God has given us.

05:47.129 --> 05:54.379
The Bible says that the prayers of a righteous person are powerful and effective.

05:55.341 --> 05:56.262
Would you agree with that?

05:57.604 --> 05:58.625
Again, here's the problem.

05:59.106 --> 06:02.290
Many of us in the room, many of us watching online tonight,

06:03.138 --> 06:05.842
We struggle because we don't see ourselves as righteous.

06:08.687 --> 06:11.031
We see ourselves as faulty at best.

06:12.433 --> 06:12.674
Why?

06:12.874 --> 06:14.737
Because we know the real us.

06:16.540 --> 06:18.644
We know the us when nobody else is looking.

06:18.684 --> 06:20.907
We know the us that thinks up here.

06:21.148 --> 06:24.674
We know the us that responds in ways that we really shouldn't respond.

06:24.694 --> 06:27.759
We know the us that does things that we really shouldn't do.

06:27.979 --> 06:29.682
So we look at scriptures like,

06:29.794 --> 06:37.082
The prayers of a righteous person are powerful and effective, and we think my prayers have no power whatsoever.

06:37.142 --> 06:40.546
Why try?

06:42.668 --> 06:45.651
Why should I even give it any effort?

06:46.552 --> 06:47.974
Well, here's what I wanted us to understand.

06:48.214 --> 06:59.026
When we're talking about the prayers of a righteous person, and we're gonna talk really in depth about this in a couple of weeks, what we have to understand is we're not righteous because of us.

07:01.442 --> 07:01.782
Come on.

07:03.424 --> 07:06.008
I'm not made righteous because I'm a good person.

07:07.630 --> 07:13.196
You're not made righteous because you volunteer for this organization or that organization.

07:13.256 --> 07:18.763
You're not made righteous because you choose to say the right things at the right time.

07:20.966 --> 07:24.370
The Bible says that our righteousness is like filthy rags.

07:25.872 --> 07:31.058
I don't have the time, the night to explain what that really, really means, but if you dig in as nasty.

07:32.706 --> 07:34.211
Come on, those of you that know, you know.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.264
Have you ever tried to clean something up with a dirty rag?

07:38.284 --> 07:41.294
I shared it a couple Sundays ago.

07:41.354 --> 07:43.922
I was doing some caulking.

07:44.290 --> 07:45.611
in my living room.

07:45.631 --> 07:50.355
And I got some brown caulk because I wanted to kind of fix some areas and hide some areas.

07:50.475 --> 07:52.117
Come on, anybody ever try to hide something?

07:52.257 --> 07:52.677
Yeah.

07:52.697 --> 07:56.000
So I was trying to hide some areas of some work that I've done.

07:56.060 --> 07:59.904
And so I was trying to put that brown caulk in there so I could just kind of hide that in there.

07:59.964 --> 08:02.125
And I got a little bit too much over here.

08:02.145 --> 08:04.608
So I grabbed my rag and I started to wipe it.

08:04.628 --> 08:07.450
The problem is it got more over here on the rag.

08:07.470 --> 08:10.393
So when I began to wipe this side, more caulk got over there.

08:10.413 --> 08:11.594
And then I began to wipe that.

08:11.814 --> 08:13.335
And now I just smeared over here.

08:13.675 --> 08:14.276
And before you know,

08:14.256 --> 08:15.518
and I had to repaint.

08:20.264 --> 08:20.544
Why?

08:21.426 --> 08:23.709
Because I was trying to clean something with a dirty rag.

08:25.571 --> 08:31.760
Sometimes in our walk with Christ, we try to clean up a mess with our filthiness.

08:33.662 --> 08:37.627
We try to make things right through our mistakes.

08:39.149 --> 08:42.514
And God says, I've given you a way out.

08:44.386 --> 08:49.314
Our righteousness is not in us, but in Christ.

08:51.317 --> 08:57.167
The Bible says that if we confess our sins that God's faithful and just to forgive us of all of our sins and cleanse us from what?

08:57.607 --> 08:59.330
All unrighteousness.

09:01.033 --> 09:06.802
Again, not because of us, not because we have the magic word, not because we do the right thing,

09:06.946 --> 09:36.932
but because of the price that Jesus paid on the cross of Calvary, and we look at this scripture that says, the prayers of a righteous person are powerful and effective, and then we remember the moment where Jesus looked at the disciples and says, when I go away, you're gonna do even greater things than I do, and we realize that the two of those go together, and because of what Jesus has done, because of the price that he paid, because of his willingness to sacrifice it all, we have an opportunity to step

09:36.912 --> 09:40.857
We've been to this place of righteousness, not because of us, but because of Him.

09:40.917 --> 09:50.049
When we begin to lean in to Jesus, oh, there's something about that name.

09:52.232 --> 10:01.864
When we begin to simply reach out, there's a woman in the Bible referred to as the woman with the issue of blood, how would you like for that to be your reference for all time?

10:02.826 --> 10:06.130
She has no name, it's not like Sally walked into the crowd.

10:06.466 --> 10:20.806
No, no, no, the woman with the issue of blood, but this woman was so desperate to get into the presence of Jesus, that she pressed in through the crowd, not even getting Jesus' attention.

10:20.886 --> 10:32.522
She just thought, if I can just touch the hem of his robe, if I can just touch his clothing, I believe that the bleeding in my body will stop.

10:34.305 --> 10:35.186
I want you to know,

10:36.098 --> 10:40.583
that when she touched his clothing, she was instantly healed.

10:41.243 --> 10:48.651
There's something that happens when you step into the presence of Jesus.

10:49.972 --> 11:03.986
When you allow him to change the chaotic atmosphere that you're hanging out in, come on, some of y'all know, when you step out just for a moment to say, Lord, I wanna,

11:04.130 --> 11:19.650
bypass this to step into where you are because when the atmosphere changes, when the presence of the Lord is there, the Bible says there is freedom, some translations say there's liberty.

11:21.633 --> 11:23.395
Some of you need freedom tonight.

11:25.838 --> 11:32.146
At the conclusion of the service, we're gonna end a little bit different tonight because nobody has lunch to run off to.

11:34.562 --> 11:38.267
Come on, nobody has, we don't have a second service that we have to get ready for.

11:39.168 --> 11:43.974
But we're gonna end this service tonight by having a moment of prayer.

11:45.535 --> 11:52.164
I'm gonna invite people to come to the front and we're gonna, because I believe in this room tonight, God brought you here for such a time as this.

11:52.244 --> 11:54.747
I don't think you're here by happenstance.

11:54.787 --> 11:56.369
I don't think you're here by mistake.

11:56.429 --> 11:59.753
I don't think you just kind of tripped in to be in here tonight.

11:59.773 --> 12:04.018
There's a reason why God prompted you to come out on a Friday night

12:04.546 --> 12:07.129
on a cold, cold winter's evening.

12:08.271 --> 12:12.256
I believe that tonight God wants to work in some hearts and some lives.

12:12.276 --> 12:14.739
That God wants to show up in this place.

12:15.200 --> 12:16.542
Okay, so our text, here we go.

12:16.902 --> 12:21.088
Our text tonight is found in Hebrews chapter 10 verse 19.

12:21.749 --> 12:24.292
This is what we're gonna use as our launching pad.

12:24.312 --> 12:27.917
We're gonna kind of reference back to it throughout the message this evening.

12:28.197 --> 12:32.082
It simply says this, and so dear brothers and sisters,

12:32.354 --> 12:39.625
We can boldly enter heaven's most holy place because of the blood of Jesus.

12:40.846 --> 12:51.041
Come on, we can boldly enter in heaven's most holy place because of the blood of Jesus.

12:51.142 --> 12:55.087
I don't know about you, but for me, that's a game changer.

12:55.268 --> 12:56.850
Prayer doesn't begin

12:57.186 --> 12:59.651
by some obligation I have to.

12:59.691 --> 13:08.969
He doesn't say you must, you have to, but he says you can enter in.

13:09.771 --> 13:13.458
Prayer begins because we have access.

13:14.498 --> 13:16.762
