13:30.663 --> 13:34.269
I love how the message paraphrase reads this.

13:35.270 --> 13:42.962
He says, so friends, we can now without hesitation walk right up to God.

13:43.938 --> 13:45.380
into the holy place.

13:46.903 --> 13:53.433
Jesus has cleared the way by the blood of his sacrifice, acting as our priest before God.

13:54.534 --> 13:58.020
The curtain into God's presence is his body.

13:59.822 --> 14:00.423
So let's do it.

14:01.225 --> 14:06.232
Full of belief, confident that we're presentable inside and out.

14:07.494 --> 14:12.562
Let's keep a firm grip on the promise that keep us going.

14:13.506 --> 14:15.889
He always keeps his word.

14:16.450 --> 14:18.532
I wanna challenge you tonight.

14:19.333 --> 14:23.298
I wanna challenge you to approach prayer with an open heart.

14:24.760 --> 14:28.624
Some of you, maybe you've never really had a moment with prayer.

14:28.664 --> 14:30.947
Maybe you've had a prayer of desperation.

14:31.328 --> 14:32.249
God help!

14:34.572 --> 14:34.972
Right?

14:35.853 --> 14:39.858
But you've never just had that conversation.

14:41.666 --> 14:45.852
Perhaps you think to yourself, well, I don't know how to pray.

14:46.753 --> 14:49.396
I don't know the right words to say.

14:49.557 --> 14:54.663
I don't have all the fancy lingo and fancy terminology.

14:54.683 --> 14:57.928
I'm not sure that I would even pray correctly.

14:57.948 --> 14:59.350
Well, here's a deal.

14:59.370 --> 15:01.232
There's not a right way or a wrong way.

15:03.355 --> 15:08.041
We're just called to step boldly into the presence of God.

15:09.643 --> 15:11.666
Just to have a conversation

15:12.546 --> 15:12.987
with him.

15:13.147 --> 15:15.932
God's not looking for some big fancy lingo.

15:15.972 --> 15:18.517
You don't have to, okay, this is going to be a big relief.

15:18.537 --> 15:20.100
