Why wouldn't I when the door has already been opened?

22:06.656 --> 22:08.378
Rather than saying, do I pass or do I?

22:08.598 --> 22:15.545
If I wanna be a follower of Christ, if I have to follow Christ, if I've made this decision to follow Christ, do I have to pray?

22:15.605 --> 22:18.968
Rather than saying that, ask yourself, why wouldn't I?

22:21.050 --> 22:22.852
Why wouldn't I have a conversation?

22:23.173 --> 22:24.594
Can I be honest with you?

22:24.738 --> 22:31.347
When my wife and I first started dating, if we hadn't had conversations, now truth be told, a lot of our conversations were over email.

22:32.249 --> 22:33.350
That's romantic, isn't it?

22:35.233 --> 22:35.834
Yeah.

22:35.854 --> 22:37.276
We didn't have cell phones back then.

22:37.316 --> 22:40.260
Now it costs money to call on the telephone.

22:40.280 --> 22:44.626
You had to call after seven o'clock if you were gonna call, you know what I'm saying?

22:44.646 --> 22:45.507
Remember those days?

22:45.688 --> 22:46.028
Come on.

22:48.111 --> 22:53.138
But if I didn't take the time to have conversation with my wife, what form of relationship would we have?

22:54.082 --> 22:55.363
it wouldn't work very well, would it?

22:57.126 --> 23:12.544
Yet we come into a place, we come into church, we have a moment with God, we come to an altar, we give our life to Him, we ask Him to come in and forgive us, and we think, well that's the end of the road, I've accomplished a task, I've done what I need to do, I have fire insurance, I'm going to heaven.

23:15.467 --> 23:21.554
And yeah, that's the on-ramp, that's the response of giving our lives to Christ,

23:21.634 --> 23:23.856
From that, we are to work out that salvation.

23:23.876 --> 23:27.259
We're gonna do what we need to do to grow in our faith.

23:28.260 --> 23:31.103
Now, when we work out our salvation, that doesn't mean that I've gotta earn my way.

23:31.544 --> 23:32.665
The price has already been paid.

23:33.505 --> 23:34.667
Jesus already made a way.

23:35.688 --> 23:37.930
But God says, why not come into my presence?

23:39.131 --> 23:41.954
Why not spend time talking with me?

23:43.235 --> 23:44.416
He wants to hear your heart.

23:45.257 --> 23:46.097
Does he already know?

23:46.138 --> 23:48.600
Yes, but he wants to hear it from you.

23:49.681 --> 23:50.802
How many of you parents

23:51.106 --> 23:57.153
ever had a conversation with your kids, and you already knew what the answer was, but you wanted to hear it from them.

23:58.555 --> 24:00.237
Come on, it doesn't matter how old the kids are.

24:00.257 --> 24:09.348
I've got young mamas in the room going, come on, preach a pastor, and I've got those of you that are older than me going, I remember those days where you already knew the answer.

24:09.388 --> 24:17.899
You knew what they were gonna say, but you wanted them to get to that place of admitting it, of understanding it, of recognizing it.

24:18.560 --> 24:20.562
You wanted them to really grasp

24:20.674 --> 24:23.418
The sincerity, the seriousness of that moment.

24:24.339 --> 24:25.560
I think that's kind of how God is.

24:27.623 --> 24:28.885
He already knows what we're going through.

24:29.025 --> 24:31.308
He already knows how your day was before you even tell him.

24:33.010 --> 24:34.052
You don't have to fake your way.

24:34.092 --> 24:37.576
You don't have to like come in, gritting your teeth, going, it's been a terrible day.

24:37.677 --> 24:39.199
God, I praise you, Hallelujah.

24:41.982 --> 24:44.786
He just wants to know your heart.

24:46.242 --> 25:01.728
And here's the great thing about this conversation with God, the more that we get to know Him, or the more that He gets to know us, the more time we spend with Him, the more that we get to know Him, the deeper that relationship gets, the more time that we want to spend with Him.

25:02.709 --> 25:04.252
So that brings us to our second truth.

25:04.593 --> 25:07.858
Prayer is personal, not secondhand.

25:08.994 --> 25:11.516
Prayer is personal, not secondhand.

25:11.556 --> 25:20.825
One of the greatest dangers in the modern church is what Pastor Mark Batterson in the book Whisper calls secondhand spirituality.

25:21.346 --> 25:21.927
Look what he says.

25:22.327 --> 25:28.093
At some point, most people settle for secondhand spirituality.

25:28.973 --> 25:35.420
But listening to those who listen to God is no substitute for seeking him yourself.

25:36.641 --> 25:37.842
Come on, let me say that again.

25:37.986 --> 25:44.075
Listening to those who listen to God is no substitute for seeking Him yourself.

25:44.335 --> 25:51.125
If you become reliant upon others for inspiration, that's called spiritual codependency.

25:52.567 --> 25:54.750
God wants to speak to you.

25:56.392 --> 25:56.893
Yes, you.

25:59.236 --> 26:05.906
I wonder tonight, have you ever become guilty of living your journey with God through spiritual

26:06.018 --> 26:10.502
codependency or even secondhand spirituality.

26:11.904 --> 26:15.927
We think, well, I'm just gonna spend time listening to that podcast.

26:15.947 --> 26:21.032
I'm gonna spend time listening to that sermon by that pastor online.

26:21.072 --> 26:28.519
There's so much available today, things streaming online, podcast reels, all sorts of things.

26:28.559 --> 26:29.680
I don't misunderstand me.

26:29.920 --> 26:35.826
Those are incredible things that if you look at my phone tonight, I've got several pastors in podcasts

26:35.938 --> 26:42.867
that I follow, but that cannot take the place of our one-on-one time with God.

26:45.010 --> 26:46.772
Let me throw this little thing out there also.

26:47.112 --> 26:48.454
Be careful who you listen to.

26:49.695 --> 26:54.401
Just because they have a microphone and a camera doesn't mean they're spiritually accurate.

26:57.646 --> 26:57.806
Come on.

26:57.826 --> 26:58.487
How do you know?

26:58.547 --> 27:01.931
How do you know if they're spiritually accurate?

27:02.592 --> 27:04.274
You've got to get to know God's word.

27:05.922 --> 27:11.948
And if you really don't understand quite yet, talk to somebody that's one step further than you in their spiritual journey.

27:13.030 --> 27:16.994
Ask them, is this guy that I'm listening to?

27:17.034 --> 27:17.815
Are they legit?

27:20.297 --> 27:20.798
Let me move on.

27:22.660 --> 27:24.582
I could give you some examples tonight, but I won't do that.

27:25.763 --> 27:26.304
You're welcome.

27:27.465 --> 27:27.825
All right.

27:30.508 --> 27:35.794
It doesn't mean the invitation for conversation is null and void.

27:36.066 --> 27:40.373
have the opportunity, we have the invitation, we can come boldly.

27:41.294 --> 27:51.411
It's important to note that spiritually, you cannot live off borrowed encounters or even survive off somebody's personal time with God.

27:51.551 --> 27:55.718
Prayer is simply where your faith becomes personal.

27:57.561 --> 27:58.342
Did you hear me tonight?

27:58.763 --> 28:00.946
Prayer is where your faith

28:01.442 --> 28:02.363
becomes personal.

28:02.403 --> 28:11.836
Romans 12, verse 12 says, rejoice in our confident home hope, be patient in trouble, and keep on praying.

28:12.376 --> 28:15.881
One translation says, be faithful in your prayer.

28:16.802 --> 28:18.124
It doesn't say be impressive.

28:19.426 --> 28:22.630
It doesn't say be fancy or even eloquent.

28:22.770 --> 28:25.614
It says be consistent, be faithful.

28:26.114 --> 28:28.818
That's all that God desires from us.

28:29.762 --> 28:36.372
So how do we know that prayer really should be personal and that prayer is really for every one of us?

28:36.452 --> 28:39.217
Well, let me give you a couple opportunities to grab ahold of this.

28:39.297 --> 28:41.901
First off, 1 Corinthians chapter six says this.

28:42.502 --> 28:46.168
Don't you realize that your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit?

28:46.188 --> 28:48.211
Now we're gonna do a little biblical math.

28:48.832 --> 28:50.595
You guys ready for a good equation tonight?

28:51.075 --> 28:57.906
So our bodies are the temple, we could say house of the Holy Spirit.

28:58.466 --> 29:09.825
And then in Matthew, when Jesus is turning over the tables in the temple, it says, Jesus said to them, it is written, my house shall be called a house of prayer.

29:10.286 --> 29:12.610
Now I'm gonna do a little equation here.

29:12.750 --> 29:20.082
If we are the temple of the Holy Spirit, we are the house, the residence thereof,

29:20.194 --> 29:24.543
And Jesus said, my house shall be called a house of prayer.

29:24.603 --> 29:26.828
You pull those together and guess what?

29:27.249 --> 29:30.134
Should we not be a people or a house of prayer?

29:32.299 --> 29:34.103
Come on, here he doesn't say church.

29:38.532 --> 29:41.618
He's talking about weird to be a house of prayer.

29:44.066 --> 29:48.473
And yeah, I understand that Jesus was talking actually about the temple in that moment.

29:49.034 --> 29:55.864
They had turned it into money changers and they were cheating in their sales and all sorts of things going on.

29:56.665 --> 30:06.981
But I believe that as we look at this, we can apply it to ourselves tonight and realize that Jesus is calling us to a place of complete surrender and prayer to him.

30:08.102 --> 30:13.170
Truth number three is this, prayer requires intentional listening.

30:13.922 --> 30:19.231
Now, here's the part that many of us struggle in when it comes to prayer.

30:19.792 --> 30:30.248
If he's in chapter six, verse 18 says, pray in the spirit at all times and on every occasion.

30:31.370 --> 30:34.696
First Thessalonians says, never stop praying.

30:34.876 --> 30:41.106
And we look at these verses and many of us would respond to that by going, how is that possible?

30:42.434 --> 30:46.818
I don't know how I can spend my entire day in prayer.

30:46.898 --> 30:49.701
I don't know how I can pray on every occasion.

30:50.002 --> 30:50.962
I've got a job.

30:51.023 --> 30:51.923
I've got a family.

30:51.943 --> 30:52.644
I've got to eat.

30:52.864 --> 30:54.706
I've got all of these things going on.

30:54.766 --> 30:58.910
I'm just not sure that I can pray in the Spirit at all times.

30:58.930 --> 31:01.673
I don't know that I can pray without ceasing.

31:01.913 --> 31:04.216
I'm not sure how this is possible.

31:05.477 --> 31:06.698
Here's what I want to grab a hold of.

31:08.480 --> 31:10.642
Prayer is as much listening

31:11.618 --> 31:12.540
as it is speaking.

31:15.126 --> 31:19.536
There's a reason why the Bible says, be still and know that I am God.

31:21.421 --> 31:24.348
Because if we're being honest, most of us aren't good listeners.

31:25.230 --> 31:26.272
Don't look at your husband.

31:27.595 --> 31:28.818
Don't do that.

31:29.954 --> 31:42.747
Yeah, many of us, in fact, earlier today, I had gone down, we're in a tri-level house and I'd gone down to the very lower level of our house and I was taking care of some things down there, putting some things in the freezer and feeding the cats and all that.

31:43.207 --> 31:48.853
And apparently my wife was hollering for me and she didn't care enough to come down and find out I was okay.

31:48.873 --> 31:51.456
I could have had a stroke and died right there, but that's okay.

31:51.736 --> 31:54.198
I get back upstairs and she goes, did you hear me?

31:54.459 --> 31:57.682
And I said, no, she said, I even said selective hearing,

31:59.362 --> 32:01.265
And I'm like, I didn't hear that either.

32:04.169 --> 32:13.283
Sometimes we have selective hearing even in our conversation with God because we want to hear what we like.

32:16.968 --> 32:19.973
We don't necessarily want to hear what we need.

32:21.836 --> 32:24.961
The Bible says, my God will supply all of your needs.

32:26.683 --> 32:28.626
God's going to give you what you need.

32:28.738 --> 32:30.520
Maybe that's a word.

32:30.540 --> 32:31.361
Maybe that's an encouragement.

32:31.381 --> 32:33.663
Maybe that's a correctness or a correction.

32:35.004 --> 32:38.688
We've got to be willing to say, Lord, I listen to you.

32:38.728 --> 32:40.449
God, I open my ears.

32:40.770 --> 32:43.012
I think there's a reason why we have two ears and one mouth.

32:44.914 --> 32:48.437
Perhaps we are supposed to listen twice as much as we speak.

32:50.339 --> 32:50.779
Could be?

32:51.620 --> 32:52.781
Well, Jesus said it this way.

32:53.042 --> 32:55.064
My sheep listen to my voice.

32:55.324 --> 32:57.586
I know them and they follow me.

32:58.818 --> 33:00.861
How do you get to know the voice of God?

33:01.062 --> 33:03.065
How do you get to really know Him?

33:03.105 --> 33:06.991
You spend time listening to Him.

33:08.995 --> 33:19.091
Can I just tell you if my wife calls me on my phone, even if my caller, even if she had a caller ID blocked and I said no ID when she called in, I would know it was my wife.

33:20.874 --> 33:21.095
Why?

33:21.175 --> 33:22.797
Because I know her voice.

33:24.680 --> 33:25.682
I've spent time with her.

33:28.578 --> 33:32.584
God's saying, if you'll just spend time with me, you'll get to know me.

33:32.604 --> 33:33.586
You'll know my voice.

33:34.928 --> 33:36.751
It's going to require that you slow down.

33:36.771 --> 33:38.573
It's going to require that you're still.

33:38.633 --> 33:41.277
It's going to require that you simply listen.

33:41.598 --> 33:44.482
Again, this is intentional listening.

33:44.522 --> 33:50.051
The word intentional literally means done on purpose or deliberately.

33:50.091 --> 33:54.738
Again, Mark Batterson.

33:55.330 --> 33:58.594
In the book, he says this, listening doesn't happen by default.

33:59.676 --> 34:00.837
It happens by design.

34:04.161 --> 34:16.577
You have to ruthlessly eliminate distractions and you have to turn some voices down or tune them out altogether.

34:17.979 --> 34:23.346
Some of us are letting the wrong voice speak the loudest in our ears.

34:25.730 --> 34:28.254
There are things that are taking us down the wrong path.

34:28.274 --> 34:33.622
There are things that are causing us to doubt our relationship or even calling with God.

34:33.642 --> 34:36.446
There's things causing us to doubt the love of God.

34:36.667 --> 34:40.392
There's things causing us to doubt the direction that God is taking us on.

34:40.633 --> 34:48.064
And God said, if you'll silence that noise, if you'll deliberately turn it off and listen to Him.

34:49.306 --> 34:52.050
It's making room or even creating space

34:52.258 --> 34:56.082
for God to step into your everyday ordinary situations.

34:56.322 --> 35:04.611
That's what we talk about in Romans chapter 12 when we're reminded to offer our ordinary everyday life to give it to God.

35:04.872 --> 35:06.573
That's what he desires for us.

35:06.774 --> 35:12.099
That we come to the place and we say, Lord, help me to be a better listener to you.

35:12.159 --> 35:15.483
There's a song that we sing and I love.

35:16.624 --> 35:20.348
And it says, the more I seek him, the more I find him.

35:20.368 --> 35:22.130
The more I find him, the more I love him.

35:23.522 --> 35:31.754
I want you to know tonight that the more time you spend in God's presence, the more time you're going to want to spend with Him.

35:32.996 --> 35:39.306
But sometimes we fail to be silent because, well, not because of the busyness or not even because of all the noise.

35:39.686 --> 35:43.873
Sometimes we've created this self-created fear.

35:45.595 --> 35:46.677
Again, Mark says this.

35:47.278 --> 35:52.786
One reason we turn a deaf ear to God is because we're afraid of what He's going to say.

35:54.114 --> 35:58.004
But that's because we don't know his heart toward us.

35:59.749 --> 36:01.835
Would you offer yourself to God?

36:01.855 --> 36:03.700
Would you get to know him?

36:04.081 --> 36:06.066
Would you know his hearts?

36:06.818 --> 36:16.667
See if we step back into our text, we're reminded that we can step boldly, we're given the opportunity, we're handed in the keys, we can step boldly into his presence.

36:16.887 --> 36:25.355
It doesn't say step in fearfully or step in out of concern, but boldly step into the presence of God.

36:25.916 --> 36:26.176
Why?

36:26.556 --> 36:27.337
Because he's good.

36:29.219 --> 36:30.280
Because he's faithful.

36:31.861 --> 36:34.364
Because his grace is sufficient.

36:34.424 --> 36:36.786
Because his mercies are new.

36:37.026 --> 36:37.807
every morning.

36:37.847 --> 36:42.872
I want to challenge you, silence the noise and give time to God.

36:43.573 --> 36:52.263
Finally, number four tonight, silence is not the absence of God, but an invitation for engagements.

36:52.283 --> 36:54.185
Maybe you've made this statement before.

36:54.585 --> 37:02.834
I've tried praying before, I've tried having a conversation with God before, and He didn't say anything.

37:05.122 --> 37:08.467
If you want to find out a moment where somebody dealt with that, read the book of Job.

37:09.889 --> 37:11.671
Or if you're new to the Bible, maybe you call it job.

37:12.412 --> 37:13.333
But it's Job.

37:13.914 --> 37:14.395
It's Job.

37:14.916 --> 37:19.762
There were moments of silence when he did not hear the response of God.

37:19.782 --> 37:24.569
But what I want you to know is this, silence in your prayer with God is not God ignoring you.

37:24.609 --> 37:31.218
It's not even a wall of resistance, but it's an opportunity for spiritual engagement.

37:31.778 --> 37:34.521
Silence is anything but passive waiting.

37:34.782 --> 37:37.345
It's proactive listening.

37:37.405 --> 37:45.916
And if we're being completely transparent, listening is a lot harder than talking.

37:47.858 --> 37:49.000
Have you ever met that person?

37:49.100 --> 37:50.762
Do you think, do they ever shut up?

37:53.786 --> 37:54.947
Some of you pointed at people.

37:56.289 --> 37:57.551
Yeah.

37:57.571 --> 38:00.114
There are people that every one of us know that we're like,

38:00.674 --> 38:02.436
Do they ever run out of words?

38:04.819 --> 38:09.584
And I think sometimes in our conversation with God, God says, would you just, just stop.

38:11.366 --> 38:12.907
Yes, people up front are going, shut up.

38:13.228 --> 38:14.369
Hopefully you're not talking to me.

38:14.389 --> 38:18.574
Okay, whew, shut up, pastor.

38:19.495 --> 38:22.478
No, sometimes we just need to be still.

38:22.858 --> 38:25.501
If I was to write a translation of the Bible, I'm not going to.

38:25.721 --> 38:30.066
But if I was, I would translate that scripture, be still a no, sit down and shut up.

38:30.882 --> 38:31.824
That's what I would say.

38:32.885 --> 38:36.111
Because I think that's where we falter a lot of times.

38:36.331 --> 38:40.358
We don't take the time just to listen to God.

38:41.540 --> 38:43.182
We're terrible listeners.

38:43.323 --> 38:43.563
Why?

38:43.783 --> 38:44.545
Well, two reasons.

38:45.386 --> 38:48.732
One, number one, because we're consumed by too much noise.

38:50.795 --> 38:54.962
How often do we allow the wrong voices to be the loudest that we hear?

38:57.090 --> 39:10.970
Henry Noah and once said it this way, every time you listen with great attentiveness to the voice that calls you the beloved, you will discover within yourself a desire to hear that voice longer and more deeply.

39:12.872 --> 39:24.449
The more time we spend with God, the more that we will want to hear his voice, the more that we get to know him, the more that we understand his heart, the more that we understand his heart, the more we want to become in alignment with him.

39:24.509 --> 39:25.490
Number two.

39:26.594 --> 39:27.956
were terrible at sitting still.

39:28.697 --> 39:40.015
I did a quick search, and back in the 80s and 90s, the best time on planet Earth, I'm told that our attention span was measured in minutes.

39:40.556 --> 39:47.147
Sometimes, if the situation was just right, our attention span could span upwards of 10 minutes.

39:48.409 --> 39:54.098
But today, for adults, our attention spans are eight to 12 seconds.

39:55.714 --> 39:57.536
for teenagers, it's seven to eight.

39:57.596 --> 39:59.018
I'm glad it's not six to seven.

40:01.640 --> 40:02.541
It's seven to eight.

40:05.104 --> 40:16.417
We've somehow gotten to the place where our attention span is so short that we really don't give God the time that he needs because we're consumed with so many things.

40:16.477 --> 40:25.106
Have you ever been guilty of, you've started praying and 10 seconds into your prayer, suddenly you hear,

40:25.218 --> 40:53.810
and your phone goes off or maybe somebody calls or you suddenly think of that thing that you forgot about when you're talking to your wife earlier that morning and you suddenly remembered what it was or that person's name finally came to the forefront of your mind and you thought of it in that moment why because we chase squirrels but we've got to come to the place that we learn

40:54.434 --> 40:55.896
to spend time with God.

40:57.699 --> 40:58.380
Is it natural?

40:59.541 --> 41:01.845
No.

41:01.865 --> 41:14.744
It's not natural to spend that much time focused in on one thing, but the more we get to know Him, the deeper and the greater that relationship truly is.

41:16.887 --> 41:21.714
So again, the question that we've got to ask, do I have to pray?

41:25.218 --> 41:28.902
I heard somebody whisper, yes, well, truthfully the answer is no.

41:30.323 --> 41:38.991
You don't have to pray to earn God's favor, but you get to pray because His grace, His love and His mercy have already been given to you.

41:40.473 --> 41:48.421
You don't have to pray because you gave your life to Jesus, but you get to pray because He first loved you.

41:50.603 --> 41:53.906
Hebrews chapter four says, so let us come boldly

41:54.338 --> 41:57.282
to the throne room of our gracious God.

41:57.562 --> 42:01.768
Because of Jesus, we have direct access to the Father.

42:01.828 --> 42:04.171
God is building His church.

42:04.191 --> 42:09.318
He desires to build His church through that of a house of prayer.

42:09.499 --> 42:11.481
He desires to use us.

42:11.521 --> 42:16.368
So the question is not, do I have to pray or is prayer required?

42:16.648 --> 42:20.473
The question is, will you take God up on His invitation?

42:22.576 --> 42:23.858
That's the question.

42:24.002 --> 42:24.983
to ask yourself.

42:26.866 --> 42:28.849
Yeah, prayer is one of our core values.

42:28.889 --> 42:31.392
We value prayer and not just mere chatter.

42:32.574 --> 42:34.216
We don't just want to talk about the issue.

42:34.256 --> 42:36.018
We don't want to just talk about the blessing.

42:36.038 --> 42:37.501
We want to lay to the feet of God.

42:37.521 --> 42:41.406
And I wonder will you allow that core value?

42:41.466 --> 42:46.212
Will you allow it to become part of the DNA of your life?

42:47.214 --> 42:53.202
And will you say, God, I accept your invitation this week.

42:54.466 --> 42:55.427
I'm gonna encourage you.

42:57.490 --> 42:59.011
Set a new habit in your life.

43:00.834 --> 43:03.497
Set time aside daily.

43:03.557 --> 43:07.101
I'm not saying start with an hour and a half.

43:07.141 --> 43:09.244
I'm not saying start even with 30 minutes.

43:09.324 --> 43:11.967
Maybe you need to start with eight to 12 seconds.

43:14.951 --> 43:17.254
Or better yet, surpass that, go to 15.

43:19.516 --> 43:20.117
Crazy.

43:21.759 --> 43:24.242
But just set some time aside.

43:25.410 --> 43:37.790
Not for eloquent speech, not for fancy terminology, but just to have a conversation with God, I say, Lord, speak to my life.

43:38.631 --> 43:51.231
And as you begin to pray, maybe you wanna even take some time, pray for about half the time and the rest, say, Lord, for the next three minutes.

43:51.251 --> 43:53.074
God, I just wanna listen to you.

43:54.978 --> 44:01.189
And I'm gonna be honest, that first time you do that, that three minutes is gonna feel like an eternity.

44:02.451 --> 44:02.792
It will.

44:05.376 --> 44:08.923
But the more you seek Him, the more you find Him.

44:10.425 --> 44:14.392
The more you find Him, the more you love Him.

44:16.256 --> 44:17.618
Here's what I wanna do tonight.

44:21.442 --> 44:28.849
We're gonna wrap up the service in just a second, but I told you on the front side that we're gonna put into practice a little bit of what we just talked about.

44:31.191 --> 44:36.537
I wanna encourage you in just a few moments just to leave your seat.

44:36.577 --> 44:38.298
Maybe you need prayer tonight.

44:38.318 --> 44:39.479
Maybe you need healing.

44:39.780 --> 44:41.021
Maybe you need provision.

44:41.101 --> 44:43.764
Maybe you need some restoration in your family.

44:43.804 --> 44:49.589
Maybe whatever the need may be, you need God to show up.

44:49.609 --> 44:50.450
We wanna pray with you.

44:51.458 --> 44:56.465
But maybe you're here and you say, Pastor, I just wanna spend some time with God.

44:56.686 --> 44:59.530
We have altars at either side of this building.

45:01.733 --> 45:11.067
Maybe you just want you and you alone, you with God, you wanna find a place and you wanna spend time with Him.

45:12.990 --> 45:14.592
Just a few minutes, we're gonna open these altars.

45:16.495 --> 45:17.857
Before we do that, will you join me in prayer?

45:17.917 --> 45:18.578
God, right now.

45:20.322 --> 45:21.443
Lord, speaking to our hearts.

45:22.725 --> 45:26.649
Lord, these next few moments perhaps are gonna take some of us out of our comfort zone.

45:27.750 --> 45:28.792
We've never gone to an altar.

45:28.852 --> 45:31.214
We've never responded to an altar call.

45:31.234 --> 45:32.996
We've never come forward for prayer.

45:34.819 --> 45:37.842
But Lord, tonight we understand the importance of prayer.

45:39.204 --> 45:41.366
Lord, you've offered us an invitation.

45:44.209 --> 45:48.434
Lord, you've given us an opportunity to respond to you.

45:51.202 --> 45:53.009
What would make yourself real in this place?

45:54.716 --> 45:55.920
In Jesus' name we pray.

45:58.049 --> 45:58.450
Amen.

